Consider that within the workplace, competition and cooperation are both necessary aspects of a modern workplace.  There are too many other factors, including where competition and/or cooperation is implemented, how it is implemented, why, and many more questions, that determine whether an employee, team or company is successful.  Determining the best applications of competition and cooperation is the factor that makes or breaks people.  China is like a tech giant, say Google or Apple, that has broken down the complexities of the modern world and as a result is now leading the way in the 21st century.
